# Review: Codex v0.5 ADR gate - 2026-07-05

## Verdict

Do not adopt ADR-001/002/003 as written.

ADR-002 is adoptable after a small but explicit Book II rewrite. ADR-001 and
ADR-003 are individually promising, but together they currently leave an open
P1: size-priced ATP needs `size(z)` / `size(resolve(h))`, while lazy spine
resolution wants not to resolve dead data. v0.5 needs one shared abstract
machine before either rule becomes law.

